At 2:24 today I had to say goodbye to Rocky, my best friend, the only family I had. Before you ,I was alone and you saved me so many times in different ways. You licked my tears , held my hand , and sat with me through everything. I’ve been blessed to have you. You are by far the most interesting soul. You  were so human. You’d roll your eyes, side eye me , smile . Everything. The times you’d sit on my lap forgetting that you are a dog. The times you’d steal my food when I left the room. Knock my phone out my hand when you wanted me to pet you. Watch tv with me . Check on me. All the times I got you alone and pleaded that if you could talk I wouldn’t tell anyone. I’m missing every moment. I can barely type this .I am so mad at you right now because I told you to at least wait for me to come back so I see you again . I didn’t just mean physically. Even though you were already gone today I’m glad I got to hug pet and kiss you one last time . I’m never getting over this. You’ve given my life meaning. You gave me 8 years worth of reasons to keep going and if I could I’d switch places because you deserve forever. I had the best good boy ever.  I hope that you’re having a better time in heaven now. And I hope we meet again in every life. Thank you for everything you have done. I love you more than anything . see you soon Rocky🐾🦴
Problems hit the gym , they all work out🤍
With each grave , I think of loss and I can only think of you…

September 1

My 20s have been nothing but difficult learning experiences. I’m a completely different person and for a while I argued with myself on whether or not that was a positive thing. Honestly I’ve fallen in love with myself in a different way. Im resilient asf, my ambition is unmatched, I’m a great friend , lover , auntie and mentor etc . I have so much to live for , I’ve lived more than ever. Loved harder than ever, taken so many risks , accomplished so much and lost more than I could’ve imagined in such a small amount of time. However I’ve realized that’s part of the growing process and if I’ve learned anything , it’s that life is extremely short and with that knowledge there’s no point in wasting your time in places , with people , or on things that don’t make you happy. Good or bad I’m grateful for it all. These next 365 are personal. Happy 23 to meeeeee🎂
